Desigirl-NSFW

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Noticed that most models produce either non-Indian looking women, or if prompted, produce very dark skin tones, which some, but not all Indian women have. This textual inversion tries to address that. This model produces photo-realistic women with Indian skin-tone, facial features, and body types.

Produces NSFW images unless used with very low weightages, or forced through prompts like ((clothed)).

Will likely follow up with a SFW/ mixed version.

Bad_NegAnatomy Textual Inversion

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

his is a Textual Inversion I have created, this is mainly useful to improve your overall aesthetics and character anatomy.

I don't really have a suggested weight range for this, because it really depends on what model, lora and how complicated your prompt will be. These elements can effect how much weight you will need, I usually start without any weight just to see how much it effects my generations.

The images I have generated are purely just prompts and my Textual Invertion, I only switch around the checkpoint model to test the effect.

You can try more different variation and you can get even better results then I do, as this was just some testing.

Shania Twain (2000s)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

A commission of @Zorglub.

Shania Twain is a Canadian singer and actress known as the Queen of Country Pop. She's one of the best selling musicians of all time and a winner of 5 Grammy Awards.

1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (shtw41n:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, leopard print suit with hood, leopard print top, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6, redhead, (hood on:1.2)".

Sophia Bush

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Embedding of actress Sophia Bush, known for her cheekiness and her raspy voice. You might have seen her in series such as One Three Hill or Chicago PD.

512x512 or 512x768 works best.

30ish steps DPM++ 2M KARRAS

CFG 7-8

I recommend not using hires fix but using the new Controlnet 1.1 / Ultimade SD upscaling with tiles, as it preserves her dimples and face complexity better. Hires fix tends to make her face look too even which takes away from the likeness.

Anna Tatu

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

A commission of @psytrancehero.

Anna Tatu is a Czech adult model who has featured in several movies and magazines produced by Playboy.

This is a 1200-step TI trained on a dataset of 12 images with my usual settings.

Why 12? Because I tried first with my usual 18 and I couldn't get the eyes right. I trained up to 4200 steps (probably my record high in the last couple of months) and... well, there was no fixing it, so I went back to the dataset, removed 6 suspicious pics and didn't add any new ones. Then retrained from scratch and I'm pretty satisfied with the final result, although I may keep working on it at a later point. Oh, and fair warning: this TI is very NSFW, given the source material, so if you don't want to see any nudity, please prompt accordingly.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. This textual inversion was trained off images of the western wall of Room 57 of the British Museum.

Levant_57 is the text prompt to call.

I prefer DDIM Sampler with CFG Scale 8
